      "content": "Escrow, in the context of a real estate closing, is essentially a neutral third-party holding place for funds and documents. Think of it like a secure, temporary holding area managed by a trusted professional, like a lawyer or a title company. It's used to ensure that both the buyer and the seller fulfill their obligations before the transaction is finalized, protecting both parties from the risk of one side backing out after money has been exchanged. This process keeps the deal moving smoothly and securely to the finish line.",
