      "content": "The money is typically held by a specialized escrow agent, which could be a title company or a law firm, rather than just a standard bank account. These professionals are legally obligated to manage the funds according to the terms of the purchase agreement. They act as a fiduciary, meaning they must act in the best interest of both buyer and seller, which is a high standard of trust and responsibility. This structure is designed specifically to prevent misappropriation of funds.",
