      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the buyer and seller hit a snag at the last minute, the escrow agent doesn't just let the money sit there indefinitely. They act as a mediator, following a strict protocol outlined in the initial contract. If an agreement cannot be reached, the escrow instructions will typically dictate a specific procedure, which usually involves the entire transaction being terminated, and the funds are then returned to the rightful parties. The escrow agreement provides the roadmap for how to unwind the deal if things go sour.",
